the Middle Ages and forward.

00:30:14.900 --> 00:30:17.370
And they collected this to archive

00:30:17.370 --> 00:30:20.350
that was called Himmler's
Hexenkarrochek.

00:30:20.350 --> 00:30:23.780
Why did they do this?

00:30:23.780 --> 00:30:28.920
You could say that the Nazi,

00:30:28.920 --> 00:30:34.340
that Nazi Germany was probably
the only regime in history

00:30:34.340 --> 00:30:36.980
that was positive to witches.

00:30:36.980 --> 00:30:44.500
They loved witches and they often
described them like Nordic amazons.

00:30:44.500 --> 00:30:50.250
The Nazi interest in witches
is that, especially the SS,

00:30:50.250 --> 00:30:55.390
they saw the witch hunts and
the burnings of witches as part

00:30:55.390 --> 00:30:59.210
of a larger war between
civilizations.

00:30:59.210 --> 00:31:06.770 position:56%
The witches were victims in a war
between the Catholic, Semitic Church

00:31:06.770 --> 00:31:10.070 position:56%
and the true Nordic faith and myths.

00:31:10.070 --> 00:31:16.060 position:56%
It was a way for the Catholic Church
to destroy the true Nordic religions

00:31:16.060 --> 00:31:23.490
and ideas in the SS perspective.

00:31:23.490 --> 00:31:27.910
The other person that was
responsible for the looting

00:31:27.910 --> 00:31:31.700
and maybe the most serious
collector is the man

00:31:31.700 --> 00:31:35.460
in the hat here, Alfred Rosenberg.

00:31:35.460 --> 00:31:40.760
He's one of the lesser-known
persons in the Nazi elite

00:31:40.760 --> 00:31:43.910
but I think some of
the most important.

00:31:43.910 --> 00:31:48.140
In the early 1930s Hitler
appointed him the role

00:31:48.140 --> 00:31:54.500
as the Party's spiritual
leader, the chief ideologist.

00:31:54.500 --> 00:31:58.800
And Rosenberg's mission
