00:32:58.770 --> 00:33:01.820
without institutions

00:33:01.820 --> 00:33:05.210
and he especially looked
at the Catholic Church.

00:33:05.210 --> 00:33:08.710
He meant that what
would Christianity be

00:33:08.710 --> 00:33:14.730
without the Catholic Church,
the power of this institution?

00:33:14.730 --> 00:33:19.960 position:56%
Would the Christian faith even exist
today without this institution?

00:33:21.020 --> 00:33:26.840
Rosenberg meant to create
such new Nazi institutions

00:33:26.840 --> 00:33:32.500
and he believed the two most
important areas were education

00:33:32.500 --> 00:33:34.620
and science.

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:39.970
Already during the 1930s the
Nazis started to experiment

00:33:39.970 --> 00:33:42.710
on special elite schools.

00:33:42.710 --> 00:33:47.380
They created the Adolf Hitler
Schools for young, gifted boys.

00:33:47.380 --> 00:33:50.810
Then they went to the
Ordensburgen Schools.

00:33:50.810 --> 00:33:54.990
It was like a military academy
where a boy should read Goethe

00:33:54.990 --> 00:33:57.060
and shoot the machine gun.

00:33:57.060 --> 00:34:01.570
You should be what the Nazis
would describe as poetic warriors.

00:34:01.570 --> 00:34:06.330
And they would finish
their education

00:34:06.330 --> 00:34:15.080
at Rosenberg's crown jewel, the
University of the Nazi Party.

00:34:15.080 --> 00:34:18.880
This was a school that was
planned to be built in the south

00:34:18.880 --> 00:34:21.730
of Germany after the war.

00:34:21.730 --> 00:34:29.350
And here the Nazis would create the
future leadership of Nazi Germany

00:34:29.350 --> 00:34:31.950
and secure it, the future.

00:34:31.950 --> 00:34:36.340
But these institutions
would also be the head

00:34:36.340 --> 00:34:42.540
of the other pillar,
research and science.

00:34:42.540 --> 00:34:48.360
Connected with university
