00:34:48.360 --> 00:34:53.130
institutions, spread out over
Germany that would study some

00:34:53.130 --> 00:35:01.390
of the Nazis' favorite questions,
Indo-German, German history,

00:35:01.390 --> 00:35:07.750
folk history, Celts,
Eastern research for example.

00:35:07.750 --> 00:35:12.980
And it was for, mainly for
this kind, these institutions,

00:35:12.980 --> 00:35:18.230
the institutes that the Nazis, that
the Rosenberg organization looted.

00:35:18.230 --> 00:35:24.030 position:56%
But there was only one of these that
was officially open during the war,

00:35:24.030 --> 00:35:28.950
the last one, the Institute
of the Jewish Question.

00:35:28.950 --> 00:35:35.010
And this was an institute
and a question

00:35:35.010 --> 00:35:40.050
that Rosenberg meant couldn't
be, had to be dealt right now.

00:35:40.050 --> 00:35:46.780
And it was actually opened in
1941 when the Holocaust started

00:35:46.780 --> 00:35:53.850
